  "text": "In this section, we explain how the different eigenvalue distributions for different values of s examined in Sec. 2 influence the convergence behavior of an iterative method to solve Eq. [CITATION_1] . For each of s = −1, 0, +1, we discretize Eq. (8) using the FDFD method for the system illustrated in Fig. 1 with an x-polarized electric dipole current source placed at the center of the simulation domain. We then solve the discretized equation by an iterative method to observe the convergence behavior. The iterative method to use in this section is the general minimal residual (GMRES) method [CITATION_2] , which is one of the Krylov subspace methods [CITATION_3] . We use GMRES without restart because the system is sufficiently small.",
